2011-08-08  Christopher Faulet  <christopher@yakaz.com>

	Version 0.3.1

	* ebin/yaws_syslogger.appup.in: Support live upgrade from 0.3.0 to
	0.3.1.

	* src/yaws_syslogger.erl: Fix bug when remote user is
	retrieved. It may be undefined, so we must be sure that it is a
	string.

2011-07-01  Jean-Sébastien Pédron  <jean-sebastien@yakaz.com>

	Version 0.3.0.

	The application is renamed to yaws_syslogger. This was needed to avoid
	a clash with a new module, "yaws_logger", in Yaws 1.90. The Debian
	package is now named yaws-syslogger.

	While here, bring autotools and Debian package cleanups from "bones".

2011-03-21  Christopher Faulet  <christopher@yakaz.com>

	Version 0.2.1

	* ebin/yaws_logger.appup.in: Support live upgrade from 0.2.0 to
	0.2.1.

	* src/yaws_logger_app.erl: Add function to get/set parsed access
	logformat. When we get it, if it is undefined, we re-parse it.

2011-01-25  Christopher Faulet  <christopher@yakaz.com>

	Version 0.2.0

	* ebin/yaws_logger.appup.in: Support live upgrade from 0.1.0 to
	0.2.0.

	* src/yaws_customlog.erl: Add module to parse log format for
	access messages.
	* src/yaws_logger.erl: Use the result of yaws_customlog module to
	log access messages.
	* src/yaws_logger_app.erl, ebin/yaws_logger.app.in.in: Add the
	environnement variable access_logformat to customize the format of
	access messages.

